  "prompt": "How is school changing in the 21st century in Taiwan?",
  "response": "In the 21st century, Taiwan's education system has been undergoing significant changes:\n\n1. Technology Integration\n- Increased use of digital learning tools\n- Implementation of smart classroom technologies\n- Emphasis on digital literacy and computer skills\n\n2. Curriculum Reforms\n- More focus on critical thinking and creativity\n- Reducing exam-oriented learning\n- Introducing more flexible and interdisciplinary learning approaches\n\n3. Bilingual Education\n- Promoting English language learning\n- Goal of becoming a bilingual nation by 2030\n- Increasing English instruction in schools\n\n4. Personalized Learning\n- More student-centered teaching methods\n- Adaptive learning technologies\n- Encouraging individual learning paths\n\n5. Entrepreneurship and Innovation\n- Introducing entrepreneurship education\n- Promoting STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics) subjects\n- Developing innovation and problem-solving skills\n\n6. Global Perspective\n- Increasing international exchanges\n- Encouraging cross-cultural understanding\n- Preparing students for a globalized workforce\n\n7. Mental Health Awareness\n- Greater focus on student well-being\n- Reducing academic pressure\n- Implementing stress management programs\n\nThese changes reflect Taiwan's efforts to modernize education and prepare students for the challenges of the 21st-century global economy.",
